docs.text: fifth grader joshua beal ( joseph cross ) is in the middle of a moral crisis .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: his beloved grandfather ( robert loggia ) has died , and joshua has begun a quest .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he wants to find god , to discover why bad things happen .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this religious quest is slightly disturbing for his parents ( dana delany and denis leary ) , but they do their best to cope with their son as he explores different religious faiths .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: at his catholic school , his favorite teacher , sister terry ( rosie o'donnell ) , tries to give him guidance , but this is a journey he must make on his own .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: meanwhile , he is having the most momentous year of his life .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he has several adventures with his daredevil best friend dave ( timothy reifsnyder ) , he gets his first crush , and begins to wake up to the world around him while he is on his spiritual journey .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it is somewhat confusing as to what the real audience for wide awake is expected to be .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: on its surface , it appears to be a kid's film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: however , it deals with serious issues , and is likely to be boring for today's instant-gratification kids .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and while it might seem heartening to see that someone is trying to produce something thoughtful for the kidvid audience , wide awake asks serious questions , but only delivers a cheap gimmick for an answer .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: if there were a bit more meat in the story , adults on a nostalgic bent might get a kick out of the movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the actors who might have created a great cast ( o'donnell , leary and delany ) are wasted in roles that amount to little more than cameos .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the nostalgic elements ( best friend , favorite teacher , first crush , etc . ) have been done much better in other movies , and actually seem more like filler here .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the film's strongest scenes are some touching flashbacks depicting joshua's relationship with his grandfather .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: they show more depth than is present anywhere else in the movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: maybe the film would have been better if , instead of playing the relationship through flashbacks , it were set entirely during joshua's last year with his grandpa .
docs.label: negative
